glosses: to sneak in, wind into (ideas etc.)

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish صوقمق (sokmak, “to insert; to bite, sting”), from Proto-Turkic *sok- (“to pierce, stick into”). Cognate with Azerbaijani soxmaq, Karakhanid سُقْماق (suqmāq), Kazakh сұғу (sūğu), Kyrgyz согуу (soguu), Southern Altai согор (sogor).
